---
import ChapterShell from "../../../components/ChapterShell.astro";
import { localePath } from "../../../lib/i18n";
import Section from "../../../components/Section.astro";
import DiagramFigure from "../../../components/diagrams/DiagramFigure.astro";
import EvidencePipelineKeystone from "../../../components/diagrams/EvidencePipelineKeystone.astro";
import FourRepsFlow from "../../../components/diagrams/FourRepsFlow.astro";
import ActivePruneFlow from "../../../components/diagrams/ActivePruneFlow.astro";
import SourceChainFlow from "../../../components/diagrams/SourceChainFlow.astro";
---

<ChapterShell chapterId="02" locale="en">
  <div slot="thesis">
    <p>
      When a Tool call both changes the world and emits a huge payload, how do you keep evidence of
      what happened without crushing the next inference in the same Turn? The answer is not blunt
      truncation — separate fact, raw bytes, evidence, and context, then hold:
      <strong>Prune the context, never prune the evidence.</strong>
    </p>
  </div>

  <Section
    id="scene"
    label="§02 · Scene"
    title="Start from a gigantic test log"
    lede="The same Tool Result plays many roles — one JSON blob cannot carry all of them."
  >
    <p>
      Suppose the model calls Bash and tests dump 80,000 lines. The system must simultaneously: show
      the model the critical errors, leave replayable facts in the Runtime, retrieve the full raw
      text when needed, and keep the next step of the same Turn from carrying the entire original.
    </p>
    <p>
      Stuffing forever into the prompt wrecks the budget; deleting destroys auditability; letting the
      model claim “I verified” mixes observation with judgment. The real question: what must be
      durable, what can be rebuilt, and what should live only briefly in the model’s working set?
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section
    id="keystone"
    label="§02 · Keystone"
    title="Turn-level evidence pipeline"
    lede="Scene-local metaphor; the fixed system is NewsLiquid tokens, hand keystones, and motion discipline."
  >
    <DiagramFigure
      prototype
      caption="Fig. 1 · A Tool Result splits into four representations; active prune rewrites Provider messages only — never Evidence."
      alt="Pipeline from Tool execution to Runtime Event, Artifact, Turn Evidence, then Provider messages; 01–04 persist as evidence; 05 may be pruned; invariant: Prune the context, never prune the evidence."
    >
      <EvidencePipelineKeystone />
    </DiagramFigure>

    <p class="figure-note">
      Invariant: <strong>Prune the context, never prune the evidence.</strong>
      The pipeline metaphor is local to §02 — not a site-wide composition rule.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section
    id="four"
    label="§02 · Four representations"
    title="One Tool Result, four representations"
    lede="Evidence compression may change how the model later sees a fact — not whether the fact occurred."
  >
    <DiagramFigure
      caption="Fig. 2 · Same result as Durable Fact / Raw Artifact / Turn Evidence / Ephemeral Working Context."
      alt="Four columns: Runtime Fact, Artifact, Turn Evidence, Working context."
    >
      <FourRepsFlow />
    </DiagramFigure>
    <ul class="plain-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Canonical Runtime Fact</strong> — what was called and returned (durable RuntimeEvent)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Raw Artifact</strong> — where the full payload lives (own lifecycle and checksum)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Turn Evidence</strong> — bounded, source-bearing observations worth later consumption
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Model Working Context</strong> — the minimum the next step must see (ephemeral; may
        prune)
      </li>
    </ul>
    <pre class="code-block" aria-label="Four-layer pipeline">Tool execution
  → RuntimeEvent(function_call / function_response)
  → Artifact(raw payload)
  → TurnEvidence(source-bearing bounded projection)
  → Provider Messages(current working set)</pre>
    <aside class="history-aside">
      <p class="history-aside__tag">Evolution aside</p>
      <p>
        Turn Evidence / active prune architecture chapter land:
        <a href={`${localePath("en", "history/pr/769")}`}>maka:pr:769</a>.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </Section>

  <Section
    id="turn"
    label="§02 · Boundary"
    title="Why Turn is the natural Evidence boundary"
    lede="Steps are too fine; Sessions are too wide; Turn is the operable midpoint."
  >
    <DiagramFigure
      caption="Fig. 4 · Source chain: RuntimeEvent → Artifact → Turn Evidence → later consumers; raw remains fetchable."
      alt="Four steps: RuntimeEvent, Artifact ref, Turn Evidence, Later consumer."
    >
      <SourceChainFlow />
    </DiagramFigure>
    <p>
      Model/tool events in this round share a turnId; tool call/result, permission, and artifacts can
      belong to the same round; a Turn terminal fact marks completed / failed / aborted. The next
      Turn can treat prior Evidence as bounded engineering memory without expanding every raw dump.
    </p>
    <p>
      Evidence describes sourced observations; it does not replace Runtime terminal status, nor claim
      “an official verifier certainly passed.” Authoritative conclusions live elsewhere (see §05).
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section
    id="current"
    label="§02 · Current"
    title="Active prune rewrites Provider messages only"
    lede="Inside the same Turn, before the next step is assembled; on failure, prefer token cost over deleting the ledger."
  >
    <DiagramFigure
      caption="Fig. 3 · Active prune: archive raw → bound view → rewrite provider messages; Evidence stays."
      alt="Five steps: Large result, Archive raw, Bound view, Rewrite msgs, Evidence untouched."
    >
      <ActivePruneFlow />
    </DiagramFigure>
    <p>
      On the Current path, ToolRuntime remains the side-effect boundary; RuntimeEvents store the
      canonical semantics of tool interaction. Active Tool Result Prune runs between provider steps:
      it only handles large finished results in the current Turn, replaces provider-visible messages
      with bounded summaries/pointers, and <strong>does not rewrite</strong> the committed Event Log
      / Artifacts.
    </p>
    <p>
      Compact Evidence appears on Headless heavy-task paths, but a general TurnEvidence envelope
      (full source linkage, shared across surfaces) remains Target — labeled below so proposals are
      not written as shipped.
    </p>
    <div class="stub">
      <p class="stub__tag">Current vs Target</p>
      <p>
        Current: active prune + RuntimeEvent/Artifact fact boundary. Target: unified TurnEvidence
        envelope and full source chain. Teaching and figures center the invariant; Target is not
        disguised as implemented.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <div slot="outline">
    <ul class="outline-list">
      <li>Keystone + four-reps + active prune + source chain</li>
      <li>
        Aside: <a href={`${localePath("en", "history/pr/769")}`}>maka:pr:769</a>
      </li>
      <li>Current prune/event boundary vs Target TurnEvidence envelope labeled</li>
      <li>Acceptance checklist hard gate met (zh+en same ship)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ChapterShell>

